The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at an event celebrating 70 years of Israel's independence. Pence expressed gratitude for President Donald Trump's support of Israel and mentioned the opening of the American Embassy in Jerusalem. He also discussed the United States' commitment to confronting terrorism and its withdrawal from the Iran nuclear deal. Pence praised Israel's accomplishments and expressed confidence in its future. He concluded by expressing his belief in the strength of the U.S.-Israel relationship.